ANTHRAX: WHAT EVERY CLINICIAN SHOULD KNOW
---------------------------
If you missed the live satellite broadcast on 18 Oct 2001, single copies of
the program are available free of charge on VHS videotape. You can order by
phone 1-877-252-1200 (011-301-645-7773 for international calls), fax
(301-843-0159), e-mail (<info@phf.org>), or on-line at
<http://bookstore.phf.org/prod172.htm>
Additional copies may be purchased in packages of 5 copies for $35. There
is a 15% discount on orders of 20 or more 5-packs (i.e., 100 videos). Order
multiple copies at
<http://bookstore.phf.org/prod173.htm>
The archived version of the webcast is available at
<http://www.sph.unc.edu/about/webcasts/bioter_10-18_stream1.htm> on the
University of North Carolina School of Public Health web site. Please note
that RealPlayer Version 8 or higher is required. Visit:
<http://proforma.real.com/real/player/player.html?src=011011realhome_1,01101
1rpchoice_h1&dc=101910181017>
or click on RealPlayer link at
<http://www.phf.org/anthraxHTML.htm>
for a free downloadable copy of RealPlayer.
The program presents clinical guidelines and procedures for the early
recognition, diagnosis, treatment, and reporting of anthrax exposure. A
panel of experts from the CDC provides an overview of clinical, laboratory
and public health preparedness for potential _Bacillus anthracis_
incidence. Sponsored by the American Hospital Assn., American Medical
Assn., Public Health Training Network, CDC, and the University of North
Carolina School of Public Health.
CDC PUBLIC HEALTH EMERGENCY PREPAREDNESS & RESPONSE
<http://www.bt.cdc.gov> contains bioterrorism fact sheets, guidelines,
notification protocols, news, Frequently Asked Questions, links, and more.
Includes information about CDC roles and national programs such as the
National Pharmaceutical Stockpile and the Health Alert Network.
NATIONAL LIBRARY OF MEDICINE - MEDLINEPLUS HEALTH TOPIC ON ANTHRAX
The National Library of Medicine at NIH has created a Medlineplus health
topic page on anthrax. Medlineplus is the NLM's consumer health information
service. The new page was released October 18. It contains targeted links
to pertinent information at CDC, other federal agencies, professional
associations, media reports, prefab Medline searches, and more. The URL is
<http://www.nlm.nih.gov/medlineplus/anthrax.html>
--
